title: Better error message for deep recursion (overflow)

labels.name: A-debuginfo
labels.description: Area: Debugging information in compiled programs (DWARF, PDB, etc.)

labels.name: C-enhancement
labels.description: Category: An issue proposing an enhancement or a PR with one.

labels.name: A-diagnostics
labels.description: Area: Messages for errors, warnings, and lints

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
From #39684:

```
use std::iter;

fn silly<I: Iterator<Item=()>>(it: I) {
    silly(it.chain(iter::empty()))
}

fn main() {
    println!("Start");
    silly(iter::empty());
    println!("Done");
}
```

```
warning: function cannot return without recurring
 --> silly.rs:3:1
  |
3 | fn silly<I: Iterator<Item=()>>(it: I) {
  | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ cannot return without recurring
4 |     silly(it.chain(iter::empty()))
  |     ------------------------------ recursive call site
  |
  = note: #[warn(unconditional_recursion)] on by default
  = help: a `loop` may express intention better if this is on purpose
```
